subject: Re: [Read_Alphabet] Is this group defunct?
msgSnippet: You are not alone. However, this is the first email I ve gotten from this group in a very long time. Could you send me a link to the Memrise quickscript
messageBody:
You are not alone. However, this is the first email I've gotten from this group in a very long time. Could you send me a link to the Memrise quickscript course? I would be curious to look at it. Also,I could share some things I have if you don't have them.

For a while I was using quickscript to write my journal pages on paper, but I switched to writing on the computer.

For my own enjoyment, I created my own notional version of ICAO phonetic alphabet (Alfa bravo Charlie, etc.) if one had to spell things on the radio with quickscript.


On 7/9/2017 2:18 PM, tvindy@... [Read_Alphabet] wrote:
 

I seem to be a bit late to the party. I'm very interested in learning Quickscript, and I'm progressing quickly through the Memrise exercises. Is anyone else still learning or using Quickscript, or am I completely alone?
